results. Picks up below dash.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DAN SEWELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Cuban-born state Sen. <PERSON> Ileana </PERSON> <PERSON> Ros-Lehtinen </PERSON> romped to the Republican nomination Tuesday in the race to succeed the late Rep. <PERSON> Claude </PERSON> <PERSON> Pepper </PERSON>, while a Cuban-born former city commissioner and a prominent <PERSON> Jewish </PERSON> attorney headed to a Democratic runoff. Attorney <PERSON> Gerald </PERSON> <PERSON> Richman </PERSON> claimed momentum as he narrowly led a seven-candidate field in the ethnically diverse district. Former <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> city commissioner <PERSON> Rosario </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON>, also Cuban-born, had been the front-runner but was criticized for late negative campaigning. She ran just behind <PERSON> Richman </PERSON>, who in his stump speech said the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> slot was `` an <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> seat.'' Pepper's niece, <PERSON> Jo </PERSON> <PERSON> Ann </PERSON> <PERSON> Pepper </PERSON>, fell short of the Aug. 15 runoff for the District 18 seat. `` It is really incredible,'' said Ms. <PERSON> Ros-Lehtinen </PERSON>, who was carrying nearly every precinct with 80 percent-plus totals. `` We're quite humbled and really flabbergasted We really just hoped for a victory without a runoff.'' Elections officials said turnout was best in the <LOCATION> Little </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Havana </LOCATION> precincts. The Aug. 29 special election to fill the seat Pepper had held for the Democrats since 1962 could result in election of the first Cuban-American in <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. While the Democrats battle in a runoff campaign, Ms. <PERSON> Ros-Lehtinen </PERSON> will get help from a fund-raising visit Wednesday by Vice President <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> for the state <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> and she will film a new television commercial Thursday. `` We are going to charge ahead,'' she sa