<HEAD>Health Official Says Congress Responsible for Providing AIDS Funding</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto WX8</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JERRY ESTILL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> must share the responsibility in the battle against AIDS by appropriating money for all the programs it says must be implemented, a federal health official says. Dr. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> O. </PERSON> <PERSON> Mason </PERSON>, assistant secretary for health at the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Human </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>, said <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> often fails to provide additional money to pay for programs it authorizes. `` We have been getting very clear guidance except when we get an authorization without an appropriation,'' <PERSON> Mason </PERSON> told a <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> oversight subcommittee grilling him Tuesday about spending on AIDS treatment. `` It would be helpful if you folks would provide leadership,'' shot back Rep. <PERSON> Ted </PERSON> <PERSON> Weiss </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.Y. </LOCATION>, chairman of the subcommittee. Rep. <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Pelosi </PERSON>, D-Calif., said the department wo n't get a larger share of limited federal funds `` unless the department is going to squeak a lot louder. <PERSON> Weiss </PERSON> and <PERSON> Pelosi </PERSON> represent the two cities _ <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> _ with the largest AIDS populations. <PERSON> Mason </PERSON>, who headed the <ORGANIZATION> Centers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Disease </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Control </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> before being selected by <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> for the No. 2 <ORGANIZATION> HHS </ORGANIZATION> job, said he shares responsibility for the entire <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGAN