<HEAD>Political Scientist Michael Harrington Dies at 61</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Harrington </PERSON>, remembered as the `` conscience of <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'' who inspired such leaders as the Rev. <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> <PERSON> Luther </PERSON> <PERSON> King </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> and President <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON> with books about <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s poor, has died of cancer at 61. The political theorist and longtime activist died Monday night at his home in suburban <LOCATION> Larchmont </LOCATION>. The death was announced Tuesday by the <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>, where he was a professor of political science at <ORGANIZATION> Queens </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> College </ORGANIZATION>. He wrote 16 books on the problems of massive poverty in the midst of affluence and on the cultural stress associated with technological advance. In a 1987 interview with The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Harrington </PERSON> recalled how key individuals, including King and <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON>, seized upon his book, `` The Other America: Poverty in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>,'' to rally for the federal war on poverty. `` The luck was that the book came out at a time when there was a president of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> who read books, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON>, and he read it,'' <PERSON> Harrington </PERSON> said. `` It led him to decide to make poverty an issue in the 1964 campaign. `` He was killed before he could do it but that set in motion the process that led <PERSON> Lyndon </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON> to declare war on poverty.'' <PERSON> Harrington </PERSON> also was active in the civil rights movement, the anti-war movement and the movements a