 Things looked dark for 300 <ORGANIZATION> Lake </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Worth </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Utilities </ORGANIZATION> customers when the <ORGANIZATION> Postal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> lost nearly $ 40,000 worth of checks for electrical bills. But the Postal service put a little light back in the customers' lives by finding the missing checks _ three weeks and hundreds of angry phone calls later Postal Service officials acknowledge `` a failure in the postal system,'' but wo n't be more specific. The missing checks were worth $ 39,598.88. They were mailed June 23, promptly disappeared and then reappeared July 12. `` It's a shame it happened,'' <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Kindred </PERSON>, director of marketing for the post office in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Palm </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION>, said Tuesday. `` I'm sorry as all get-out about it.'' Ten customers had their electricity cut off, said <PERSON> Brenda </PERSON> <PERSON> Nedzweckas </PERSON>, business manager for the city-run utility. All 302 customers received late notices and electricity cutoff warnings. All were billed an extra $ 10 in late charges, later waived.
