<HEAD>Arts Director Says Eight Chinese Performers Will Not Seek Political
Asylum</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JENNIFER McNULTY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The director of a Chinese-American arts organization in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> said Wednesday that none of the eight Chinese opera performers who vanished last week plans to apply for political asylum. The entertainers are `` scared to death'' by the publicity their disappearance has caused, said <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> Chow </PERSON>, executive director of the <ORGANIZATION> Chinese </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION>. The fate of the entertainers, including seven opera stars and a popular actor, has been unknown since the group fled the 28-member <LOCATION> Kun </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Opera </LOCATION> company last week. Immigration officials in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> said Wednesday they had no connect with the performers. <PERSON> Chow </PERSON>, who would say only that he has `` some connection'' with the performers, reported that four remained in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>, two are in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> and two are in <LOCATION> Washingon </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION> All are staying with relatives or friends, said <PERSON> Chow </PERSON>, adding that he was uncertain whether the performers had planned to flee the opera group or acted spontaneously. Observers have speculated that the eight might be seeking democratic and economic freedoms in the wake of the student-led pro-democracy movement in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> this spring. But <PERSON> Chow </PERSON> insisted that the artists will not seek asylum. It has been common for performers from <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Taiwan </LOCATION> to arrive in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> with a working v