<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said Wednesday he will nominate <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> Read </PERSON> <PERSON> Hanmer </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> to be deputy director of the <ORGANIZATION> Arms </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Control </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Disarmament </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Hanmer </PERSON>, a retired <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> colonel, is chief negotiator for strategic offensive arms in the U.S.-Soviet negotiatons on nuclear and space arms. He would succeed <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> in the post.
