<HEAD>Salvadoran Guerrillas Attack Towns</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARCOS ALEMAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Leftist guerrillas fought overnight battles with government soldiers on <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION>'s northern outskirts, and others attacked at least four towns Wednesday Six people were reported killed and more than 10 wounded in the towns. At least one soldier and a civilian were killed and three people were wounded in the battles Tuesday night in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ramon </LOCATION> and Mejicanos, working-class areas on the city's northern edge. Venceremos, the guerrilla radio station, said the attacks on towns were part of a rebel campaign against `` the fascist government'' of President <PERSON> Alfredo </PERSON> <PERSON> Cristiani </PERSON> and `` increases in transportation costs and repression in general.'' <PERSON> Cristiani </PERSON>'s conservative administration lifted price controls on about 200 consumer items and services earlier this week, including transportation and electricity, in an effort to revive the war-battered economy. Bus fares increased Wednesday, in some cases to almost double their former levels. New electricity rates will be announced next week. Guerrillas of the rebel <ORGANIZATION> Farabundo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marti </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> has fought U.S.-supported governments for a decade. Human rights groups say more than 70,000 people have been killed, most of them civilians. Several rebel columns attacked military positions at <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pedro </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Nonualco </LOCATION>, 38 miles east of the capital, early Wednesday and one civilian was killed in the fighting, the army press office said. A Venceremos broadcast told people to stay off the road in the area because rebel forces had mined it. One rebel was killed and five were wounded in a guerrilla attack on military positions in northern <LOCATION> Chalatenango </LOCAT