be arrested on her return. `` I consider that the hunger strike ended in a great victory,'' the official <ORGANIZATION> Korean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> quoted Miss Im as saying. `` I will wage a struggle ... for my return home.'' The <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Command </ORGANIZATION> has not blocked the student's return home, but said they would consider an unauthorized crossing of the border a violation of the armistice agreement that ended the 1950-53 Korean War. Miss Im visited <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> to attend the July 1-8 World Festival of Youth and Students. She then joined a march from <LOCATION> Mount </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Paekdu </LOCATION>, at the northern end of <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>, to the border village. <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> was divided in 1945 after World War II. The 16-nation <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Command </ORGANIZATION> fought on <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>'s side in the Korean War.
