 Elsewhere in television: <LOCATION> NEW </LOCATION> <LOCATION> MAGAZINE </LOCATION> _ Av <PERSON> Westin </PERSON> has joined <ORGANIZATION> King </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Productions </ORGANIZATION> to create a new first-run syndicated news magazine show tentatively called `` 30 Minutes.'' <PERSON> Westin </PERSON> is a former <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> executive. In 1967 he was the producer of `` <ORGANIZATION> PBL </ORGANIZATION>,'' the <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Laboratory </ORGANIZATION>,'' the granddaddy of all television magazine shows.
