 The board of <ORGANIZATION> Concordia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Theological </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Seminary </ORGANIZATION> voted to retire the seminary's president, the Rev. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Preus </PERSON>, charging `` turmoil'' in the institution made him ineffective. Preus called that a `` complete fabrication.'' Head of the Lutheran Church-Missouri Synod institution for 15 years, <PERSON> Preus </PERSON> said he had not wanted to retire and contended the board's action would have a `` damaging effect on seminary income, a demoralizing effect on the student body'' and a polarizing effect the faculty. He said charges by the board that `` turmoil within the faculty'' made it impossible for him to serve effectively were false.
