 `` Salaam Bombay!'' -LRB- Virgin Vision, <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, English subtitles. VHS-Beta, $ 79.95 -RRB- `` Salaam Bombay!'' is a heartrending look at the homeless street children of <LOCATION> Bombay </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> India </LOCATION>. But its meanings and nuances transcend that exotic locale. The film, which won a number of international film awards in 1988, is a riveting portrayal of how 20th century societies, including so-called civilized ones, are devouring their young, alternately selling them, or selling them short. Producer-director <PERSON> Mira </PERSON> <PERSON> Nair </PERSON> traveled the streets of <LOCATION> Bombay </LOCATION>, fascinated by the resilience of the thousands of children who survive by their wits in a squalid world of dirt, drugs and prostitution. She decided to tell their story, not with actors, but with children she gathered from those very backstreets. `` Salaam Bombay!'' is the story of 10-year-old <PERSON> Krishna </PERSON>. Abandoned first by his mother, then by the traveling circus he joins, he travels to <LOCATION> Bombay </LOCATION> hoping to earn 500 rupees to take back to his mother. <PERSON> Krishna </PERSON> acquires street wisdom and a toughness that even leads to a murder. But somehow, almost miraculously, he keeps a child-like empathy even as he is failing in his own hopes. He befriends a desperate drug addict, and comforts an abject 16-year-old sold by her own mother to a brothel. The film's producers decided to use proceeds to establish learning centers for the street children of <LOCATION> Bombay </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Delhi </LOCATION>. `` Salaam Bombay!'' is not rated. It has no objectionable language or sexual encounters, but the themes of street life are nonetheless unvarnished. It is a truly exceptional film. _ By <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitgang </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
