 <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> corporate purchasing managers said their gauge of industrial health fell to the weakest point since the economic expansion began more than 6 -LCB- years ago, a report that fanned recession fears. The Purchasing Managers' Index, a widely watched barometer of the economy's direction, plunged to 46 percent in July from 48.8 percent in June, the third straight monthly decline, the group said Tuesday.
