fer devices that allow cars to pay tolls without stopping. But <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> T </ORGANIZATION> said it has the only card whose software allows it to be used for multiple purposes. For example, the same card could also store car maintenance records. <ORGANIZATION> Amtech </ORGANIZATION>'s system, which uses a plastic TollTag, is in operation on the <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Tollway </LOCATION>. The company is also trying to sell a system in <LOCATION> Oslo </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Norway </LOCATION>.
