red a 15 percent stake in <ORGANIZATION> ESPN </ORGANIZATION> in January 1984 and obtained the remaining 85 percent five months later from <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> after <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION>'s acquisition of <PERSON> Getty </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> ESPN </ORGANIZATION>'s visibility has been rising in recent years. It has been carrying <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Football </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> League </ORGANIZATION> telecasts for two years and acquired in January the rights to telecast 175 regular season Major League Baseball games a year for four years starting in 1990.
