<HEAD>Energy Prices Close Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Energy futures prices closed mixed Wednesday with crude oil bouncing back from earlier lows despite ongoing concern about excess oil supplies. On the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the September contract for <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> Intermediate, the benchmark grade of crude oil, rose 25 cents to finish at $ 18.28 a barrel after falling 28 cents on Tuesday. The contract had dipped to $ 17.78 a barrel during the trading session. Contracts for later delivery were mixed. Among refined oil products traded on the exchange, unleaded gasoline for September delivery fell 0.58 cent to 50.85 cents a gallon, while future contracts were mixed. Domestic heating oil for September rose 0.34 cent to 49.54 cents a gallon and other contract months were mostly higher. The market opened lower mainly on a report showing that oil and gasoline inventories are continuing to rise. The <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> said supplies of crude oil, gasoline and heating oil increased in the week ended July 28. The API report was released after the close of trading on Tuesday. Crude oil inventories rose 882,000 barrels to 331.4 million barrels from the previous week, while gasoline stocks increased by 4.6 million barrels to 225.96 million and heating oil rose by 2.1 million to 111.5 million barrels, the report said. On a yearly basis, however, crude oil stocks were down 16.9 million barrels from the same time last year and heating oil was off 6.8 million barrels. Gasoline inventories, however, were 16.3 million barrels higher. Later in the day, traders said oil prices recovered, partly on technical factors. `` The momentum just was n't there to move lower,'' said <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Redoglio </PERSON>, energy broker for <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION>. Analysts said nervousness about the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> hostage situation in the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> also helped boost prices. Traders have attributed some price strength in recent days to investor concern that political events involving <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> hostages could disrupt oil shipments from the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>.
