<TEXT>
 A jury Wednesday rejected Home Shopping Network's $ 1.5 billion lawsuit charging <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> with providing faulty telephone equipment and instead awarded $ 100 million to two <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> subsidiaries for libel and slander. The cable television retailer claimed it lost millions of calls and $ 500 million in potential sales in 1986 and early 1987 because <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> telephone equipment it contracted for could not handle the volume of calls. But after a six-week trial at <ORGANIZATION> Pinellas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>, the jury rejected charges of fraud, negligent misrepresentation, breach of trust and confidence, and breach of fiduciary duty against the telecommunications giant. Instead it awarded <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> $ 50 million each for damages to their reputation and credibility by <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Shopping </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Network </ORGANIZATION> and its two top executives on charges in a countersuit by <LOCATION> Stamford </LOCATION>, Conn.-based GTE. <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> was cited for $ 20 million of the total award with $ 40 million each against <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> Speer </PERSON> and President <PERSON> Lowell </PERSON> <PERSON> Paxson </PERSON>. Home Shopping immediately said it would appeal the decisions. The jury of four women and two men deliberated for about five hours over two days. `` We are very disappointed with the jury's verdict and we will appeal the decision immediately,'' said <PERSON> Nando </PERSON> <PERSON> DiFilippo </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION>'s executive vice president and general counsel He said the network would maintain that the court should not have presented <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION>'s libel and slander counterclaim to the jury. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> V. </PERSON> <PERSON> Carideo </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION> vice president and general counsel, said the verdict reassures `` the integrity of the companies,'' which the <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> suit `` had put at issue.'' Home Shopping merchandise may be bought by home viewers only while the item is being displayed on the screen. The network said it lost 42 million calls when as much as 50 percent of its incoming calls never got through to waiting sales operators because of the allegedlt faulty equipment. <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> filed its suit in Septmeber 1987. <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> denied any wrongdoing, contending there was nothing wrong with its equipment and it had not misled Home Shopping. <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION>'s countersuit maintained that the electronic retailer blamed the phone company for financial problems actually caused by mismanagement. The company argued that over-expansion, competition and customer dissatisfaction rather than ineffective equipment triggered <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> losses. In one year, the number of Home Shopping subscribers soared from 9 million to 46.5 million, <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> attorney <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> Reardon </PERSON> said.
