<LOCATION> Republic </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Amax </ORGANIZATION>, a supplier of metals and energy, has as its major products aluminium, coal, gold and molybdenum. The <ORGANIZATION> Falconbridge </ORGANIZATION> deal is conditioned on acceptance of <ORGANIZATION> Amax </ORGANIZATION>'s offer by at least two-thirds of <ORGANIZATION> Falconbridge </ORGANIZATION> shareholders No deadline has been set for tendering the company's 79 million fully diluted shares, the <ORGANIZATION> Amax </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman said. If the deal goes through, <ORGANIZATION> Amax </ORGANIZATION> has agreed to make an additional offer to acquire all untendered shares. <ORGANIZATION> Amax </ORGANIZATION> recently moved its headquarters from <LOCATION> Greenwich </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, but maintains corporate offices here. <ORGANIZATION> Falconbridge </ORGANIZATION> immediately implemented a shareholder rights plan to defend against hostile offers. The measures would give existing shareholders the right to purchase additional stock at a bargain rate if another party acquires at least 15 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Falconbridge </ORGANIZATION> stock. The so-called `` poison pill'' plan will expire in 120 days if the deal is not approved by shareholders, <ORGANIZATION> Amax </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Falconbridge </ORGANIZATION> said in a joint statement. The <ORGANIZATION> Amax </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman said the company abandoned the nickel business because it was only a refiner and not a miner. She said <ORGANIZATION> Falconbridge </ORGANIZATION> presented <ORGANIZATION> Amax </ORGANIZATION> with a `` quality position'' in which it will both mine and refine nickel.
