<HEAD>TBS Reports Profit Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Ted </PERSON> <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> on Wednesday credited his new all-movie cable channel, <ORGANIZATION> Turner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Network </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Television </ORGANIZATION>, with boosting <ORGANIZATION> Turner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> System </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s revenues and profit in the second quarter. Atlanta-based <ORGANIZATION> TBS </ORGANIZATION> reported net income of $ 5.5 million for the quarter ended June 30, compared with a loss of $ 25.9 million for the same quarter a year earlier. However, it reported a net loss per common share of 12 cents in this year's second quarter due to the payment of dividends and the accumulation of discount on its Class B preferred stock. Quarterly revenues were up 33 percent, to $ 264.5 million from $ 199.3 million. For the six months ended June 30, net income was $ 5.1 million, or a loss of 37 cents a share after an extraordinary item, compared with a loss of $ 40 million for the same period in 1988. Revenues were $ 496.5 million, up 30 percent from revenues of $ 381.9 million for the same period a year earlier. `` The addition of <ORGANIZATION> TNT </ORGANIZATION> to our already successful lineup of basic cable networks has lifted our quarterly operating profit to an all-time high,'' said <PERSON> Turner </PERSON>, chairman of TBS. `` We are particularly pleased that our improved performance is the result of contributions from all four basic cable networks, confirming our belief that each network remains attractive to advertisers and viewers alike,'' he said. In addition to <ORGANIZATION> TNT </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> TBS </ORGANIZATION> owns <ORGANIZATION> Cable </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Network </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> CNN </ORGANIZATION> Headline News and Superstation WTBS. The company also owns professional baseball's <ORGANIZATION> Atlanta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Braves </ORGANIZATION> and professional basketball's <ORGANIZATION> Atlanta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hawks </ORGANIZATION>.
